keycloak:openid/fullNameProtocolMapper:F.description:
Allows for creating and managing full name protocol mappers within Keycloak.

Full name protocol mappers allow you to map a user's first and last name to the OpenID Connect <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`name`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`Name`" pulumi-lang-go="`name`" pulumi-lang-python="`name`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`name`" pulumi-lang-java="`name`">`name`</span> claim in a token.

Protocol mappers can be defined for a single client, or they can be defined for a client scope which can be shared between
multiple different clients.

## Example Usage

